summary: So ive been binge watching interesting titles on netflix to get my creative juices flowing and get over a really massive art...
body:
So ive been binge watching interesting titles on netflix to get my creative juices flowing and get over a really massive art block ive been dealing with. This is a serious part of my process when im struggling to create and i felt like sharing this with the void so here we go:

- I am Sun Mu

- Saving Banksy (really made me feel like going back to street art)

- The incredible Jessica James

- Sierra Burgess is a loser

- Old Boy (I love the director)

- La Casa de Las Flores

- Las Leyes de la Termodinamica

- Adventure Time (season 5)

- To all the boys Ive loved before

If I can manage to keep away the thoughts that I should be making stuff right now, I think I can watch at least 5 other titles until sunday.

summary: A painting I did when my wrist was messed up for 3 months. I don’t know what it’s supposed to be but I love it! I always...
caption:
A painting I did when my wrist was messed up for 3 months. I don’t know what it’s supposed to be but I love it! I always hesitate on paintings because I’m afraid of “ruining” the canvas. It felt good to just let go and let the paint to what it wants. I’m hoping I can get into that headspace again so I can make another one of whatever this is!

—————–

Soooo what are your plans tonight? Are you going out? Having a nice dinner? LAME! Why spend all that money on those things when you can get some awesome art from me? C'mon man. Slide into my messages and we can make some pretty wicked sick art!
